external_knowledge:
- "notable impact" refers to the condition where the average frequency of the variants is greater than 0.001; 
- "significant clinical effect" refers to the clinical significance categories 'pathogenic' or 'likely pathogenic';
- "present in more than 0.1% of the population" refers to a frequency greater than 0.001.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS article_count
FROM pubmed_articles
WHERE journal = 'Leuk. Res.';

SELECT title
FROM pubmed_articles
WHERE journal = 'Leuk. Res.' AND year = 2010;

